 <title>The Shinkansen- Japan&#039;s Bullet Train</title>
 <link>http://www.theworldisnotflat.com/shinkansen</link>
 <description>&lt;object height=&quot;350&quot; width=&quot;425&quot;&gt;&lt;param name=&quot;movie&quot; value=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/v/O6FHFZgdReI&quot;&gt;&lt;/param&gt;&lt;embed src=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/v/O6FHFZgdReI&quot; type=&quot;application/x-shockwave-flash&quot; height=&quot;350&quot; width=&quot;600&quot;&gt;&lt;/embed&gt;&lt;/object&gt;  Today we travelled over 1000 kilometers at a rate of speed sometimes over 300 kph (186mph) on Japan&amp;#39;s Bullet Train- the Shinkansen.  Train travel has never been so cool.  &lt;br&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flickr.com/photos/leelefever/142758482/&quot; title=&quot;Photo Sharing&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://static.flickr.com/49/142758482_09aab074b4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Shinkansen- Japan&amp;#39;s Bullet Train&quot; height=&quot;375&quot; width=&quot;500&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br&gt; They just look and feel so smooth.&lt;br&gt;   &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flickr.com/photos/leelefever/142758527/&quot; title=&quot;Photo Sharing&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://static.flickr.com/51/142758527_80551626a9.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Shinkansen- Japan&amp;#39;s Bullet Train&quot; height=&quot;375&quot; width=&quot;500&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;  Hopefully the video relates the speed.&lt;br class=&quot;clear&quot; /&gt;</description>
